

# Remotion Patterns — Extracted from Production Compositions

This cookbook documents patterns that have been validated in production renders.
Use these exact implementations. Do not reinvent unless there is a clear reason.

---

## 1. FILE BOILERPLATE

### 1a. Light mode (Apple style — app demo on white/grey background)

```ts
import React from "react";
import {
  AbsoluteFill, continueRender, delayRender,
  interpolate, spring, useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig,
} from "remotion";
import { Icon } from "./Icons";
import { waitForInter } from "./fonts";

// ─── Design tokens ────────────────────────────────────────────────
const T = {
  bg: "#f8f9fa", surface: "#ffffff", sidebar: "#0e1029",
  accent: "#9db8ee", mist: "#9DB8EE", text: "#112431", muted: "#6b7280",
  light: "#a4afb7", border: "#d9dfe3",
  success: "#329547", warning: "#ffb704", error: "#ec6369", info: "#0066cc",
  font: "'Inter', sans-serif",
};

// ─── Timeline (30 fps) ────────────────────────────────────────────
// [Add inline comments describing the narrative sequence]
const TL = {
  fadeIn:    0,
  kpis:      20,
  rows:      60,
  camZoom:   120,
  action:    180,
  cta:       350,
  end:       450,
};
```

