## 4. FLEX TABLE PATTERN

Never use `<table>/<tr>`. Use flex divs with COL_W percentage array.

### Table reveal strategy — simultaneous rows, staggered badges/bars

**Rule:** Rows should appear as a complete table (simultaneous fade), NOT one by one. Only badges and progress bars pop in staggered — they add visual life without making the table feel slow to load.

```tsx
function TableRow({ row, idx, frame, fps }: {
  row: RowData; idx: number; frame: number; fps: number;
}) {
  // All rows fade in at the same time — table feels like one cohesive unit
  const rowO  = fade(frame, TL.tableIn, 14);
  // Badges and progress bars stagger in after — adds life, light stagger (6f)
  const popAt = TL.rows + idx * 6;
  const badgeSc = spr(frame, popAt, fps, { damping: 14, stiffness: 220 });

  return (
    <div style={{ display: "flex", alignItems: "stretch", height: 72,
      borderBottom: `1px solid ${T.border}`, opacity: rowO }}>
      {/* Text columns — just rendered, no animation */}
      <div style={{ ...cell(), width: COL_W[0] }}>{row.name}</div>
      {/* Badge column — spring pop */}
      <div style={{ ...cell(), width: COL_W[1] }}>
        <Badge type={row.statusType} label={row.statusLabel} scale={badgeSc} />
      </div>
      {/* Progress bar column — fills in after row appears */}
      <div style={{ ...cell({ flexDirection: "column" }), width: COL_W[2] }}>
        <ProgressBar pct={row.pct} color={row.color} frame={frame}
          startAt={popAt + 2} duration={28} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**TL.rows is not for row stagger — it's the pop anchor.** Rows all appear at `TL.tableIn`. `TL.rows` only serves as the base for `popAt = TL.rows + idx * 6`.

```tsx
