## 11. EMPHASIS RING OVERLAY

For highlighting a specific area of the screen after a camera zoom (e.g., "look at these two rows"):

```tsx
const EmphasisRings: React.FC<{ frame: number }> = ({ frame }) => {
  const o = interpolate(frame, [TL.highlightAt, TL.highlightAt + 15, TL.highlightAt + 35, TL.highlightAt + 50], [0, 0.9, 0.9, 0], clamp);
  if (o <= 0) return null;
  return (
    <div style={{ position: "absolute", inset: 0, pointerEvents: "none", zIndex: 50, opacity: o }}>
      {/* Position rings at world-space coordinates — only works when zoom = 1 or in camera space */}
      {[490, 565].map((y, i) => (
        <div key={i} style={{
          position: "absolute", left: 820, top: y, width: 160, height: 26,
          border: `2px solid ${T.error}`, borderRadius: 6,
          boxShadow: `0 0 16px ${T.error}88`,
          background: `rgba(236,99,105,0.06)`,
        }} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
// Note: if camera is zoomed when rings appear, place EmphasisRings inside camera div
// If zoom=1, place outside camera div (screen space = world space at zoom=1)
```

