## 15. CARD POP (state transition without flip)

When a new card replaces an existing card (e.g. incident card replaces detail card), avoid 3D flips. Use spring pop + opacity cross-fade.

```tsx
// Container — relative position, both cards inside
<div style={{ width: 960, height: 420, position: "relative" }}>

  {/* Front card — fades out */}
  <div style={{
    position: "absolute", inset: 0, ...cardBase, overflow: "hidden",
    opacity: fade(frame, TL.karimIn, 16) * fdOut(frame, TL.notifierIn, 12),
  }}>
    <FrontCard frame={frame} fps={fps} />
  </div>

  {/* Pop card — springs in */}
  {frame >= TL.notifierIn && (
    <div style={{
      position: "absolute", inset: 0, ...cardBase, overflow: "hidden",
      opacity: fade(frame, TL.notifierIn, 10) * fdOut(frame, TL.notifyOut, 18),
      transform: `scale(${interpolate(
        spr(frame, TL.notifierIn, fps, { damping: 18, stiffness: 170 }),
        [0, 1], [0.88, 1]
      )})`,
    }}>
      <PopCard frame={frame} fps={fps} />
    </div>
  )}

</div>
```

**Rules:**
- Pop card starts at scale `0.88`, springs to `1`. Never use `rotateY` or `perspective`.
- Both cards share the same `position: absolute, inset: 0`. The container has `position: relative`.
- The front card fades out slightly before the pop card appears — avoids both being fully visible simultaneously.
- For a "replace" feel, start pop card when front card is at ~30% opacity.

