## 21. SPRING PRESETS & EASING (from Remotion skills)

Named spring presets (use these instead of inventing configs):

```ts
// Smooth, no bounce — subtle reveals, camera moves
const smooth  = { damping: 200 };

// Snappy, minimal bounce — UI elements, badge pops
const snappy  = { damping: 20, stiffness: 200 };

// Bouncy — playful entrances (avoid in SaaS demos)
const bouncy  = { damping: 8 };

// Heavy, slow — large cards, dramatic reveals
const heavy   = { damping: 15, stiffness: 80, mass: 2 };
```

**Spring with `delay` param** (cleaner than `frame - startAt`):
```ts
// Instead of: spring({ frame: frame - TL.cardIn, fps, config })
// Use:
spring({ frame, fps, delay: TL.cardIn, config: { damping: 200 } })
```

**Spring with `durationInFrames`** — stretches spring to exact frame count:
```ts
spring({ frame, fps, durationInFrames: 24 }) // settles exactly at frame 24
```

**Easing on interpolate** — use instead of spring when motion is linear-with-curve:
```ts
import { Easing } from "remotion";

// Camera push-in — ease out (fast start, slow settle)
const zoom = interpolate(frame, [TL.camStart, TL.camEnd], [1, 1.3], {
  ...clamp,
  easing: Easing.out(Easing.quad),
});

// Custom cubic bezier (e.g. iOS spring feel)
const slide = interpolate(frame, [0, 30], [40, 0], {
  ...clamp,
  easing: Easing.bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1),
});
```

Available curves (most→least linear): `Easing.quad`, `Easing.sin`, `Easing.exp`, `Easing.circle`.
Combine with: `Easing.in`, `Easing.out`, `Easing.inOut`.

