## 25. CURSOR WORLD-SPACE POSITION FORMULA (centered card layout)

In Architecture B (frame-based), cards are centered in a `AbsoluteFill` using flex. Computing pixel coordinates for cursor targets requires tracing the layout stack.

**Formula for a card centered in 1080p with SceneHeadline above it:**

```
// Variables:
//   totalContent = sceneHeadlineH + gap + cardH
//   cardTop      = (1080 - totalContent) / 2 + sceneHeadlineH + gap

// SceneHeadline height:
//   chip:  fontSize 12 × 1.2 lineHeight + 5px×2 padding + marginBottom 20 ≈ 44px
//   title: fontSize 52 × 1.15 lineHeight ≈ 60px
//   total ≈ 104px
//
// Card body starts at: cardTop + tabBarH (if any)
// Then for a right panel with padding-top P, label heights L:
//   firstPillY = cardTop + tabBarH + P + L
//   rowN_centerY = firstPillY + (pillH / 2) + (N × (pillH + pillMarginBottom))
```

**Worked example — 2-column pill grid in right panel:**
```
cardTop      = (1080 - (104 + 32 + 464)) / 2 + 104 + 32 = 376px
tabBarH      = 44px   → body starts at 420px
rightPadding = 28px   → content starts at 448px
label "Ajouter des variables" = 11px font × 1.2 + 6mb ≈ 19px
subtitle = 12px font × 1.4 + 16mb ≈ 33px
pillsStart   = 448 + 19 + 33 = 500px
pillHeight   = 8×2 padding + 12px font × 1.2 = 30px
rowSpacing   = 30 + 10 (marginBottom) = 40px

Row 0 center = 500 + 15 = 515px
Row 1 center = 500 + 40 + 15 = 555px
Row 2 center = 500 + 80 + 15 = 595px

// Column X (2 cols, gap 10, inner padding 28, content width 520):
// colWidth = (520 - 56 - 10) / 2 = 227px
// col0 center X = cardLeft + leftPanelW + rightPaddingLeft + 227/2
// col1 center X = col0 + 227 + 10
```

**Do this math before writing the first TL, not after the first render.** Document it in a comment block above `const PILL = {...}`.

