## 26. VARIABLE PILL INSERTION (click → colored token in textarea)

Pattern for a "variable picker" panel where clicking a pill inserts a `{{ variable }}` token into a live text area.

```tsx
// State: which variables have been clicked (by TL frame)
const CLICK_MAP: Record<string, number> = {
  tenant_name:        TL.click1,
  payment_url_amount: TL.click2,
  payment_url:        TL.click3,
  agency_name:        TL.click4,
};
const isPillDone  = (key: string) => !!CLICK_MAP[key] && frame >= CLICK_MAP[key] + 5;
const pillFlash   = (key: string) => {
  const at = CLICK_MAP[key]; if (!at) return 0;
  const dt = frame - at; if (dt < 0 || dt > 18) return 0;
  return interpolate(dt, [0, 3, 18], [0, 0.25, 0], clamp); // brief mist flash
};
// Spring scale pop on click
const varSc = (at: number) =>
  at && frame >= at ? spring({ frame: frame - at, fps, config: { damping: 14, stiffness: 200 } }) : 0;

// Pill rendering (done = highlighted with mist border + bg)
<div style={{
  border: done ? `1.5px solid ${T.mist}` : `1px solid ${T.border}`,
  background: done ? `rgba(157,184,238,${0.15 + flash})` : flash > 0 ? `rgba(157,184,238,${flash + 0.05})` : "#fff",
  color: done ? T.mist : T.text,
}}>{key}</div>

// Token rendering in text area (colored inline span with spring pop)
<span style={{
  color: T.mist, fontWeight: 600,
  background: "rgba(157,184,238,0.12)", borderRadius: 4, padding: "1px 4px",
  display: "inline-block",
  transform: `scale(${varSc(CLICK_MAP["tenant_name"])})`,
  transformOrigin: "left center",
}}>{"{{ tenant_name }}"}</span>
```

**The `buildSmsSegments()` approach:** Build the full composed text as alternating `{text, isVar, varKey}` segments. The typewriter engine advances through segments in order; each `{{ var }}` segment appears instantly (no char-by-char) when its click TL frame is reached.

