## 27. PREVIEW CYCLING (cross-fading between N recipients/states)

When Step 4 (or any "aperçu") needs to cycle through N items with a cross-fade:

```tsx
const ITEMS = [
  { name: "Karim Benali",   msg: "..." },
  { name: "Fatima Ouali",   msg: "..." },
  { name: "David Marchand", msg: "..." },
  { name: "Amina Traoré",   msg: "..." },
];

// Advance the active index at pre-defined TL frames
const activeIdx =
  frame >= TL.sw3 ? 3 :
  frame >= TL.sw2 ? 2 :
  frame >= TL.sw1 ? 1 : 0;

// Each switch: equal spacing (~20f) — the cross-fade takes ~12f
// sw1 = previewIn + 34, sw2 = sw1 + 20, sw3 = sw2 + 20

// Cross-fade: compute opacity for the incoming item
const switchFrames = [TL.previewIn, TL.sw1, TL.sw2, TL.sw3];
const activeSwitch = switchFrames[activeIdx];
const previewO     = fade(frame, activeSwitch, 12);

// Render only the active item (re-mounting triggers the fade)
<div key={activeIdx} style={{ opacity: previewO }}>
  <div>{ITEMS[activeIdx].name}</div>
  <div>{ITEMS[activeIdx].msg}</div>
</div>
```

**Rule:** Space switches evenly (~20f). Don't use a long single typewriter for preview content — the text is too long and won't fit in the scene duration. Cross-fading between pre-composed strings is faster and cleaner.
